GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
S 1
SENATE BILL 747
Short Title: AI Learning Agenda. (Public)
Sponsors: Senator Salvador (Primary Sponsor).
Referred to: Rules and Operations of the Senate
March 26, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT ESTABLISHING THE OFFICE OF ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE POLICY AND
3 CREATING THE AI LEARNING LABORATORY PROGRAM.
4 Whereas, artificial intelligence technologies are transforming economies, societies,
5 and industries globally, requiring proactive exploration of their implications for North Carolina;
6 and
7 Whereas, this act establishes an iterative, stakeholder-informed learning model to
8 support thoughtful, evidence-based governance of AI technologies; Now, therefore,
9 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
10 SECTION 1. The General Assembly finds it essential to proactively explore artificial
11 intelligence technologies through an inclusive and iterative learning model that promotes
12 innovation while protecting consumer interests and civil rights.
13 SECTION 2. Chapter 114 of the General Statutes is amended by creating a new
14 Article to read:
15 "Article 11.
16 "Artificial Intelligence Learning Laboratory.
17 "§ 114-75. Definitions.
18 The following definitions apply in this Article:
19 (1) Applicant. – A person that applies for participation in the regulatory Learning
20 Laboratory.
21 (2) Learning Agenda. – The areas of artificial intelligence applications, risks, and
22 policy considerations selected by the Office established by this act for focus
23 by the Learning Laboratory.
24 (3) Learning Laboratory. – The artificial intelligence analysis and research
25 program created in this a ct.
26 (4) Office. – The Office of Artificial Intelligence Policy created in this act.
27 (5) Participant. – A person that is accepted to participate in the Learning
28 Laboratory.
29 (6) Regulatory mitigation. – When restitution to users may be required, the (i)
30 terms and conditions related to any cure period before penalties may be
31 assessed, (ii) any reduced civil fines during the participation term; and (iii)
32 any other terms tailored to identified issues of the artificial intelligence
33 technology.
34 (7) Regulatory mitigation agreement. – An agreement between a participant, the
35 Office and relevant State agencies entered into under this act.
