1 prescribe a form for use by State agencies for compilation and submission of the inventory
2 required by this subsection. This inventory shall include the following information for each
3 artificial intelligence technology included in the inventory:
4 (1) The vendor of the artificial intelligence technology.
5 (2) A description of the function and capabilities of the artificial intelligence
6 technology.
7 (3) A description of (i) the purpose or purposes for which the state agency uses
8 the artificial intelligence technology; (ii) any purpose for which the agency
9 contemplates using the artificial intelligence technology in the future; and (iii)
10 examples of the data or information produced by the artificial intelligence
11 technology for each purpose.
12 (4) Whether the artificial intelligence technology provides the agency with
13 information or data that is used by the State agency to inform decisions made
14 by the agency; or decisions, without human intervention, that are implemented
15 by the agency.
16 (5) The types of information or data used by the artificial intelligence technology
17 and the source of the information used by the artificial intelligence
18 technology.
19 (6) The manner in which the State agency secures the following from
20 unauthorized access:
21 a. Artificial intelligence technology.
22 b. Information or data used by the artificial intelligence technology; and
23 c. Information or data produced by the artificial intelligence technology.
24 (7) Any person with which the State agency shares the information or data
25 produced by the artificial intelligence technology and the purpose for which
26 the state agency shares the information or data with the person.
27 (8) The documented or anticipated benefits and risks of the state agency's use of
28 the artificial intelligence technology for both the State agency and State
29 residents served by the agency.
30 (9) Any information or data used by the State agency to assess the benefits and
31 risks of the agency's use of the artificial intelligence technology.
32 (10) The fiscal effect of the State agency's use of the artificial intelligence
33 technology, including the following:
34 a. Costs associated with the artificial intelligence technology, including
35 initial acquisition or development costs and ongoing operating costs,
36 including costs of licensing, maintenance, legal compliance, and data
37 storage and security.
38 b. Any funding source that is used, or could be used, by the state agency
39 to defray the costs described.
40 c. An estimate of the degree to which the costs described are offset by a
41 reduction in the State agency's operating costs attributable to the
42 agency's use of the artificial intelligence technology.
43 (11) Whether the artificial intelligence technology has been tested or evaluated by
44 an independent third party.
45 (12) Whether the data or information produced by the artificial intelligence
46 technology has been evaluated for bias against constitutionally protected
47 classes of individuals, found to exhibit bias, and adjusted to mitigate any such
48 bias.
49 (b) By January 1, 2027, the Office, in consultation with relevant State agencies, shall
50 conduct a comprehensive analysis of the existing regulatory governance of artificial intelligence
51 technology in the State, as follows:
